citeinfo.title: Winter Diets of Common Murries and Marbled Murrelets in Kachemak Bay, Alaska

abstract.p: Knowledge of the winter diets of seabirds in high latitudes like Alaskan waters has been an elusive aspect of their biology. Scentry information on winter diets of Common Murres (Uria algae) are available from the Pribilof Islands, California, Kodiak Islands, Newfoundland and the North Sea and for Marbled Murrelets from British Columbia and Kodiak. This paper summarizes the diets of these two species, as observed during the winter season of 1977-1978 in Kachemak Bay, Alaska, as a part of the Alaskan Outer Continental Shelf Environmental Assessment Program, OCSEAP and provides further interpretaion of the data.

[Reference: Sanger, Gerald A. Winter diets of common murres and marbled murrelets in Kachmak Bay, Alaska. May 1987. The Condor Vol. 89 No. 2 pp.426-430.] Reprint available at the NOAA Seattle NMML Library.
